The paper proposes a novel network embedding method that uses both network structure and edge attributes to learn better network representations. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Computer Science and Game Theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper mentions downstream tasks such as link prediction and node classification, which could also place it in sub-categories such as Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
